        "description": "Applications like the Spark AM currently do not run as a YARN service and setting hostname breaks driver/executor communication if docker version >=1.13.1 , especially with wire-encryption turned on.\r\n\r\nYARN-8027 sets the hostname if YARN DNS is enabled. But the cluster could have a mix of YARN service/native Applications.\r\n\r\nThe proposal is to not set the hostname when \"host\" networking mode is enabled.",
